MoldingInfo.Description: Composite plates with dimensions 200 x 80 x 3.2 mm were compression-molded at 175°C for 8 min, with a 5 min preheating period

Scanning_Electron_Microscopy.Description: SEM was used to observe the morphologies of the fracture surfaces of all composites. The specimens were coated with a thin layer of gold prior to SEM examination

Dynamic_Mechanical_Analysis.Description: DMA was conducted at a fixed frequency of 10 Hz and oscillation amplitude of 0.15 mm. The temperature range studied was from -20 to 130°C with a heating rate of 1°C/min.

Thermogravimetric_Analysis.Description: The weight loss against temperature was measured at a heating rate of 5°C/min in a helium environment from 50 to 400°C

Rheometery.Description: The capillary die used had a length (L) to diameter (D) ratio of 40/1 and an entrance angle of 180°
